      "comment": "PAW RAMELLO (7) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by half a length at Shepparton in a handy 22.23 beating Koda. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. Can measure up again. MAISEY MARY (2) was well in the market last time but only managed fifth (25.54), beaten 8 lengths. Was in the money the start prior. Shapes as one to consider. SPICE ROAD (1) turned in a better effort at this track last start, finishing third behind Patty's Dream (25.39) in a T3 RSTW. Turned chasing the leaders but kept coming. Must be included in calculations. KEIJON BARNY (3) is worth a look despite no experience at this circuit.",
